⏺ Elevator System — Complete Python Implementation

  ---                                                                                                                                                                                                           
  Step 1: Enums
                                                                                                                                                                                                                
  from enum import Enum
  from dataclasses import dataclass
  from typing import List, Optional, Set
  import math                                                                                                                                                                                                   
  import threading
                                                                                                                                                                                                                
  class Direction(Enum):                                                                                                                                                                                        
      UP = "up"
      DOWN = "down"                                                                                                                                                                                             
      IDLE = "idle"

  class RequestType(Enum):
      PICKUP_UP = "pickup_up"       # hall call, going up
      PICKUP_DOWN = "pickup_down"   # hall call, going down                                                                                                                                                     
      DESTINATION = "destination"   # button inside elevator                                                                                                                                                    
                                                                                                                                                                                                                
  Why RequestType separate from Direction?                                                                                                                                                                      
                  
  The article makes this explicit: hall calls are never IDLE, but Direction has three values including IDLE. If you reuse Direction for hall calls, you must add runtime validation everywhere: if type ==      
  Direction.IDLE: reject. With RequestType, that invalid state literally cannot exist — the type system prevents it at construction time.
                                                                                                                                                                                                                
  ---             
  Step 2: Request — Frozen, Hashable, Equality by Value
                                                                                                                                                                                                                
  @dataclass(frozen=True)
  class Request:                                                                                                                                                                                                
      floor: int  
      request_type: RequestType                                                                                                                                                                                 
  
  Why frozen=True on Request?                                                                                                                                                                                   
                  
  Requests live in a set. Python sets require elements to be hashable. frozen=True dataclasses get a free __hash__ based on all fields. Without it, you'd need to manually implement __hash__ and __eq__, and   
  mutable objects in sets lead to bugs when the object changes after insertion.
                                                                                                                                                                                                                
  Why store both floor AND request_type in Request?

  This is the key design decision from the article. If you only store floor numbers, you can't distinguish:                                                                                                     
  - Person on floor 6 going DOWN → Request(6, PICKUP_DOWN)
  - Person on floor 6 going UP → Request(6, PICKUP_UP)                                                                                                                                                          
  - Destination button pressed for floor 6 → Request(6, DESTINATION)
                                                                                                                                                                                                                
  With floor-only storage, the SCAN algorithm can't skip pickup requests that are going the wrong direction. You'd stop at floor 6 going UP to pick up someone who wants to go DOWN — they board a car going the
   wrong way.                                                                                                                                                                                                   
                                                                                                                                                                                                                
  Set membership check:                                                                                                                                                                                         
                  
  r1 = Request(6, RequestType.PICKUP_DOWN)                                                                                                                                                                      
  r2 = Request(6, RequestType.PICKUP_DOWN)
  r3 = Request(6, RequestType.PICKUP_UP)                                                                                                                                                                        
  
  print(r1 == r2)    # True  — same floor, same type                                                                                                                                                            
  print(r1 == r3)    # False — same floor, different type
  print(r1 in {r2})  # True  — set deduplication works                                                                                                                                                          
                                                                                                                                                                                                                
