  Step 5: step — The SCAN Algorithm (5 Cases)
                                                                                                                                                                                                                
  This is the interview answer. Every case must be in the right order.
                                                                                                                                                                                                                
      def step(self) -> None:
          # ── Case 1: Nothing to do ─────────────────────────────────────────────                                                                                                                              
          if not self.requests:                                                                                                                                                                                 
              self.direction = Direction.IDLE                                                                                                                                                                   
              return                                                                                                                                                                                            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                
          # ── Case 2: IDLE but has requests — pick direction ────────────────────                                                                                                                              
          if self.direction == Direction.IDLE:
              self.direction = self._pick_initial_direction()                                                                                                                                                   
                                                                                                                                                                                                                
          # ── Case 3: Stop at current floor if there's a matching request ───────                                                                                                                              
          pickup_type = (                                                                                                                                                                                       
              RequestType.PICKUP_UP                                                                                                                                                                             
              if self.direction == Direction.UP
              else RequestType.PICKUP_DOWN
          )                                                                                                                                                                                                     
          pickup_req = Request(self.current_floor, pickup_type)
          dest_req = Request(self.current_floor, RequestType.DESTINATION)                                                                                                                                       
                                                                                                                                                                                                                
          if pickup_req in self.requests or dest_req in self.requests:
              self.requests.discard(pickup_req)                                                                                                                                                                 
              self.requests.discard(dest_req)
              # Note: Request(current_floor, PICKUP_DOWN) when going UP survives.                                                                                                                               
              # It will be served on the return trip. This is correct SCAN behavior.                                                                                                                            
              if not self.requests:                                                                                                                                                                             
                  self.direction = Direction.IDLE                                                                                                                                                               
              return  # Stopped this tick — don't move                                                                                                                                                          
                                                                                                                                                                                                                
          # ── Case 4: No requests ahead → reverse ───────────────────────────────                                                                                                                              
          if not self._has_requests_ahead(self.direction):                                                                                                                                                      
              self.direction = (                                                                                                                                                                                
                  Direction.DOWN if self.direction == Direction.UP else Direction.UP                                                                                                                            
              )
              return  # Reversed this tick — don't move yet                                                                                                                                                     
                  
          # ── Case 5: Move one floor ────────────────────────────────────────────                                                                                                                              
          if self.direction == Direction.UP:
              self.current_floor += 1                                                                                                                                                                           
          else:   
              self.current_floor -= 1
                                                                                                                                                                                                                
  Why exactly this order?
                                                                                                                                                                                                                
  - Case 1 before 2: Can't pick a direction from an empty set (would crash).                                                                                                                                    
  - Case 2 before 3: Stop-check logic reads self.direction to know which pickup_type to check. If direction is still IDLE, you'd compute PICKUP_IDLE — which doesn't exist.
  - Case 3 before 4: We might be at a reversal point that also has a stop. Stop first, then on the next tick check direction.                                                                                   
  - Case 4 before 5: If we're going to reverse, we don't move this tick. Otherwise you'd move AND reverse in one tick, skipping a floor.                                                                        
                                                                                                                                                                                                                
  Why discard instead of remove?                                                                                                                                                                                
                                                                                                                                                                                                                
  set.remove(x) raises KeyError if x is absent. We're calling discard(pickup_req) and discard(dest_req) unconditionally after an or check — only one might be present. discard handles both being absent        
  gracefully.
                                                                                                                                                                                                                
  ---             
  Step 6: _pick_initial_direction — Deterministic Nearest Request

      def _pick_initial_direction(self) -> Direction:
          """
          When IDLE with requests, find the nearest request.                                                                                                                                                    
          Tie-break: lower floor number wins (deterministic across runs).
          """                                                                                                                                                                                                   
          nearest: Optional[Request] = None
          min_distance = math.inf                                                                                                                                                                               
                                                                                                                                                                                                                
          for req in self.requests:
              distance = abs(req.floor - self.current_floor)                                                                                                                                                    
              if distance < min_distance or (
                  distance == min_distance
                  and (nearest is None or req.floor < nearest.floor)                                                                                                                                            
              ):
                  min_distance = distance                                                                                                                                                                       
                  nearest = req

          return Direction.UP if nearest.floor > self.current_floor else Direction.DOWN                                                                                                                         
  
  Why not next(iter(self.requests))?                                                                                                                                                                            
                  
  set iteration order in Python is non-deterministic (depends on hash values, insertion order, Python version). Using next(iter(...)) gives a different nearest request every run, making bugs impossible to    
  reproduce. The deterministic tie-break (lower floor wins) means the same initial state always produces the same behavior.
                                                                                                                                                                                                                
  ---             
  Step 7: _has_requests_ahead — Travel vs Stop Are Different
                                                                                                                                                                                                                
      def _has_requests_ahead(self, direction: Direction) -> bool:
          """                                                                                                                                                                                                   
          Are there ANY requests above us (if going UP) or below (if going DOWN)?
          Checks ALL request types — the elevator travels toward everything,                                                                                                                                    
          but only stops for matching types.                                                                                                                                                                    
          """                                                                                                                                                                                                   
          for req in self.requests:                                                                                                                                                                             
              if direction == Direction.UP and req.floor > self.current_floor:                                                                                                                                  
                  return True
              if direction == Direction.DOWN and req.floor < self.current_floor:
                  return True                                                                                                                                                                                   
          return False
                                                                                                                                                                                                                
  Why check ALL request types (not just matching ones)?                                                                                                                                                         
  
  This is the subtle SCAN insight. Consider: elevator at floor 4 going UP, with Request(6, PICKUP_DOWN) and Request(8, DESTINATION).                                                                            
                  
  - At floor 5: has_requests_ahead(UP) → True (floor 6 and 8 are ahead). Move up.                                                                                                                               
  - At floor 6: Stop check — going UP, so check PICKUP_UP. Floor 6 has PICKUP_DOWN, not PICKUP_UP. No stop. Pass through.
  - At floor 7: Move up.                                                                                                                                                                                        
  - At floor 8: Stop check — DESTINATION at floor 8. Stop. Remove it. No more requests ahead.
  - has_requests_ahead(UP) → False. Reverse to DOWN.                                                                                                                                                            
  - At floor 6: Stop check — now going DOWN, check PICKUP_DOWN. Found. Stop. Pick up passenger.                                                                                                                 
                                                                                                                                                                                                                
  The elevator passes floor 6 on the way up. The person sees it go by — they pressed DOWN, so this is correct. It picks them up on the return. If _has_requests_ahead filtered by type, the elevator would      
  reverse at floor 5 (seeing no PICKUP_UP requests ahead) and never reach the floor 8 destination.                                                                                                              
                                                                                                                                                                                                                
