  Step 12: Thread Safety — Concurrent Hall Calls
                                                                                                                                                                                                                
  import threading
                                                                                                                                                                                                                
  controller2 = ElevatorController(num_elevators=3, num_floors=10)                                                                                                                                              
  barrier = threading.Barrier(5)
  results = []                                                                                                                                                                                                  
                  
  def hall_call(floor, rtype):                                                                                                                                                                                  
      barrier.wait()   # all 5 requests fire simultaneously
      ok = controller2.request_elevator(floor, rtype)                                                                                                                                                           
      results.append((floor, ok))
                                                                                                                                                                                                                
  threads = [     
      threading.Thread(target=hall_call, args=(3, RequestType.PICKUP_UP)),
      threading.Thread(target=hall_call, args=(7, RequestType.PICKUP_DOWN)),                                                                                                                                    
      threading.Thread(target=hall_call, args=(5, RequestType.PICKUP_UP)),
      threading.Thread(target=hall_call, args=(1, RequestType.PICKUP_DOWN)),                                                                                                                                    
      threading.Thread(target=hall_call, args=(9, RequestType.PICKUP_UP)),
  ]                                                                                                                                                                                                             
  for t in threads: t.start()
  for t in threads: t.join()                                                                                                                                                                                    
                  
  print(f"All succeeded: {all(r[1] for r in results)}")   # True                                                                                                                                                
  
  What the lock protects:                                                                                                                                                                                       
                  
  Without self._lock in request_elevator, two threads both call _select_best_elevator simultaneously, both see elevator 0 as the best option, both call elevator_0.add_request(...). Since set.add is not atomic
   in CPython under multi-threaded use, you can get silent data loss. The lock serializes select + add as an atomic unit.
                                                                                                                                                                                                                
